CAMP et al. v. PEACOCK, HUNT & WEST CO. et al. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. January 12, 1904.) No. 1,308. Appeal from the Circuit Court of the United States for the Southern District of Florida. For opinion below, see 128 Fed. 1005. J. N. Stripling, for appellants. C. M. Cooper and J. C. Cooper, for appellees.

Before PARDEE, McCORMICK, and SHELBY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

A majority of the court is of the opinion that there is no reversible error in the record. Affirmed.
